race.comment: DON'T TOUCH (3) is a boom four-year-old mare yet to taste defeat in two runs, the most recent win by 2 lengths over 1100m at Twin Hills. Comfortable winner last time and can measure up again. HI FRANK (6) showed good early speed and raced on the pace last start before fading to finish fifth, beaten 5 lengths, over 1200m at Emerald. Another bold showing is expected. BONTOBEWILD (4) got the prize two runs ago but couldn't follow that up last time out when third over 1100m at Charleville. Should be thereabouts. SHEDENZA (2) joins the new stable following a poor run at Toowoomba last time out. She's better suited back to this grade now and an improved run is on the cards.
